    "summary": "I am a monetary economist working as Climate Sector Expert at ABN AMRO Bank, Amsterdam. This position reflects my interest and passion towards the interconnection of economics and policy measures, especially related to environment and sustainability. \n\nAfter finishing my BSc. in Business Administration and Management cum laude, I pursued my first Two-year MSc in Economics, including studying one semester in the US. I then gained experience working as a banking consultant in a financial services company and developed knowledge in banking advisory on investments, insurance and creditworthiness.\n\nBeing still very interested in expanding my knowledge in economic policy-making, I decided to undertake a second Master in Monetary Policy and Banking Regulations at the Universiteit van Amsterdam. For my final dissertation, I have researched the effect of international policies on environmental performances in the financial sector. \n\nMy skill set ranges over strong quantitative skills to a good command of data analysis tools as Phyton, STATA, Dynare and Microsoft Excel.",
